<p>I hope you are right, Les.  You have a good track record, so I'm not going to dismiss it.  But I guess I've become a little cynical.<BR/><BR/>I know who controls the media -- even if 80% apparently don't (according to the ADL) -- and if Madoff is being taken down, there is damn sure a reason and a benefit for them to do so.<BR/><BR/>I run through various scenarios -- the main one is that they have to bail out these investors (as opposed to other non-Jewish ones who are shit out of luck) so they have to make him the bad guy.  The focus on the philanthropy is to show that these weren't your typical asshole rich people.  These were the rich who truly care about the little people, non-Jews even.  Most Americans are all too happy to see rich people get taken by the Wall Street ponzi scheme, too.  So, you gotta work overtime to generate sympathy.  Still, seems a little too obvious -- but then again, so is Obama's pretty much all Jewish/Zionist cabinet ...<BR/><BR/>Then, I think, if your goal is to loot the US and then lure the US -- in its dying moments -- to take out your other main competitors for nuclear/financial superpower of the world (namely Russia and China) -- a good strategy might be to completely demonize it and turn it into the next coming of the Nazi regime.  Take away the wealthy Jews' money and you have severed their connection to the US.  Then when you start building up the anti-semitism (by being over the top in Jewish appointments, only bailing out Jews who lost money, etc.), they won't balk at fleeing to Israel (where the money no doubt awaits them).  You save the "important" Jews just like in WWII and sacrifice the average Jews for the greater cause of a one world state under Jewish rule.  The rest of the world is happy to nuke us -- since Bush has made the US the poster child of evil.  And they have no idea that they have been duped into taking out a nation that was about to call them out on their duplicity and dual loyalties.<BR/><BR/>It is a brilliant plan, really.  But they suceed, not because they are more brilliant than us, but because, honestly, while it is human nature to be indifferent to the suffering of others -- it really takes a lot of conditioning to get people to sadistically enjoy another's pain.  We aren't naturally hard-wired to be that way.  Selfishness is innate.  Cruelty is not.  That is why so many people cannot accept or fathom that any group or government actively seeks to be evil.  That's why we can believe our entire goverment and military was totally inept on 9/11, but most can't accept that it was planned and executed by the US and its "allies".<BR/><BR/>Sometimes, that puts the good (or marginally more ethical -- however you want to phrase it) at a disadvantage.  But, to effectively fight them, you have to be willing to lower yourself to their level.  I think I'd rather lose with my ethics still intact.<BR/><BR/>But, if you are right, with the right help on our side, justice will give them a swift kick in the ass and we won't have to comprise our own values to see it get done.  I'm willing to suffer a little hardship in order for justice to do her thing.  That is why I'm not freaking out over another great depression.  It would suck -- but I've been poor before, I know I can survive it.  And it would be good to see the god of materialism turn and devour its most devoted servants.</p>
