<p>Okay... the first one no one will appreciate but me... because I don't think that many people know who that is around here or what's going on. I think they expect more virtuosity instead of gratitude expressed by one who is thankful to do it.<BR/><BR/>The second was hampered by poor quality but I got it.<BR/><BR/>The third one is right there and thank you.<BR/><BR/>For anyone who is interested... every year around the summer solstice I travel to a small town in Germany for a bonfire drumming ceremony. As you might suspect I engage in some things that others don't and you don't have to either but if you would like to attend just get to my house before the event and I will take you there and you'll have free room and board... any and all of you... so keep it in mind. By spring of this year you may well be wishing you would.<BR/><BR/>I don't want to diminish the contributions here by responding to one thing or another and seemingly ignoring all of the rest. I don't. I read everything. The reason I used to not ever respond here is because it always gets incestuous. There's no escaping it. I've such an intense fondness for India that I may over react about her but she is my mother although I am white and anglo as it gets besides being born a Lutheran. You have to forgive my love of India it is everything I love and that is why I am saving it until the end.<BR/><BR/>I probably haven't been the best I could be and I haven't treated all of you with the respect you deserve. I didn't want to be able to do what I can do but understand that my abilities which this is just one of them have kept me in trouble my whole life. I didn't get a breather until recently. I've had at least forty years of non stop punishing experience. I'm not looking for sympathy because other people have experienced worse.<BR/><BR/>Other people didn't even get the chance to. My road made me tough but it made me gentle too. Knowing which is required when is the art and I didn't know which for a long time.<BR/><BR/>I don't know why I'm taking the time to say this to you, my friends, this evening. I think getting a comment from India just set me off and I had to weep as many a comment has made me weep here... both for the passion and the brilliance.<BR/><BR/>People... I'm no one at all but I am so pleased that you find comfort and succor here. If only some of the stellar contributors here would join with me to forge a community we would truly have some understanding of what is possible in life during the dark necessities of this Kali Yuga. Friends, I know what is coming AND I know it doesn't have to include those of us that won't let go of our toys so... you keep in mind what I've said here and you keep in mind that you can drop your life and merge it with ours and it doesn't have to be right here where I am. It can start here and then go anywhere.<BR/><BR/>The good news is that I won't be in charge... I won't be in charge of anything but my own life and the better news is that you won't be either... we have to check our identities at the door only to discover who we really are on the other side and one of the ways we discover who we are is in each other's eyes.<BR/><BR/>I'm rambling. I wanted to say something and I screwed the pooch as usual but someone will get what I'm saying.<BR/><BR/>Look! I carry large bags of dog food in my car to feed homeless dogs who are the cast off pets of people who just want an animal companion for the summer... how much more likely is it that I would be amenable to feeding you?</p>
