<p>Visible, I am inclined to pantheism myself, but mysticism not so much as it's too easy to lose yourself there.  <BR/><BR/>If a cigar is just a cigar it becomes a question of it is a good cigar rolled between virgin thighs, or a bad cigar that is not.  We are taught to believe Cuban cigars are evil cigars and not good cigars since they come from Cuba, a communist country.  These evil cigars are much in demand by those who smoke them, some of whom created the Communism that made them evil, because they are good cigars as well . Things are not always as simple as they appear.<BR/><BR/>Alexander the Great discovered the bananna in 327 BC in India. Message: beware of evil dudes like with big banannas, what makes them happy can be bad for those they get their happiness from.  Alexander the Great did much evil to earn that title, but did this evil do good?.<BR/><BR/>One of the pantheistic laws of nature is that there is both good and evil, one can not exist without the other, as love can not exist without hate.<BR/><BR/>God is an entity that is both beyond us and within us, and he/it created the forces and laws of nature, among which is Good and Evil.  For every force there must be an equal and opposite force.  God is neither Good nor Evil but the energy created by their conflict promotes evolution, an improvement of the species and nature itself.  <BR/><BR/>Perhaps he or it has a favourite, Good or Evil, we can not know, but I think the evolution is the key, and when these opposite forces work in synergy, we evolve.<BR/><BR/>The concept of Good and Evil is the basis of dualism from which the early religions in Persia and Babylon used to corrupt Judaism during the Babylonian exile, and thus was the basis for the corruption of Christianity by the House of Herods agent Paul, and Islam was corrupted with the same ideas by the Sabians.  <BR/><BR/>In some of the ancient religions both the good and evil gods were worshipped, sometimes only the evil one if it was deemed more powerful.  The religion of the elite combines dualism with mysticism and is known in Gnosticism and Kaballah, and they believe that the god representing good to most of us is the evil one, and that representing evil to most us is the good one.  It is a truly Orwellian world.<BR/><BR/>The thinking goes that Evil was created to do Good, and allows man to evolve to be godlike, with God coming to know himself through mans battle between the forces of Good (Evil) and Evil (Good) and his subsequent evolution.  <BR/><BR/>The god the masses believe in is said to be a god who wants to keep man from the knowledge needed to evolve and become like him, and thus preventing the real God from knowing himself through man.  So say the Luciferians who seek to destroy the god of superstition and ignorance and those who believe in the religions worshipping this god.  <BR/><BR/>This will leave man free to pursue knowledge and evolve to his highest level using evil means that are not permitted by these religious beliefs that prevent man doing evil to achieve good.<BR/><BR/>Liberty is a code word of the elite which means freedom from gods (the good one which they call evil) laws.  The French and American Revolutions were the first steps by the enlightenment to free themselves from religion and the constraints imposed upon them by gods laws with the creation of secular states.  Marxism was the next step. <BR/><BR/>If you look at the wars and genocides of the last century, it was mainly religous Christians and religous Jews who were killed, and Communism was created to stamp out religion in the territory the wars allowed it to control and expanded into.  <BR/><BR/>Today of course, the target is religous Islam and perhaps the Hindu population in India, at least among the lower castes, and perhaps in the Obama years the target will move to the religous right in America, and even the Great Whore they call the Roman Catholic Church.  Tony Blairs conversion makes you wonder, doesn't it.<BR/>  <BR/>I am an adherent of no religion, but see that religion for the most part was meant to be good and fill the need of the people, but it was always corrupted by evil and taken over by evil to do evil, while pretending to do good.<BR/><BR/>I do not buy into the idea that the good angels or spirits influence one to do good and evil angels tempt us to do evil.  But however these 2 forces manifest themselves, they seem to exist, and what we call evil is kicking ass.<BR/><BR/>Now my spirit might escape my body and be free in some mystical world of other spirits, but what is left behind might not do so good, not being one of the elite.<BR/><BR/>Collectively, as man tends to approach 100% evil, or 100% good, our evolution stops. Only when there is a balance and the 2 forces struggle is there evolution.<BR/><BR/>At the present time, the Luciferian elite are in control and thus will prevent any evolution among the non-elite classes, in fact, it appears there has been a significant de-evolution, at least among the lower classes, since they do not recognize evil as such and are oblivious of any struggle so long as their credit card is accepted.  <BR/><BR/>The Luciferian elites plan is to cleanse the planet of inferior races and peoples and continue their evolution at a higher rate w/o being burdened  and hampered by what the call the genetic pollution of humans they consider less valuable than beasts.  <BR/><BR/>Alas, if Evil has no counter force to struggle against, how can they evolve?  So they will likely turn on themselves, and in the process, plunge us into the Dark Ages and End of History.  <BR/><BR/>Or perhaps they will invent some Evil that they, who will call themselves as the forces of Good, can fight.  Perhaps the idea of Gaia as a dying Goddess will prompt a massive effort to get man off this planet and explore the universe.<BR/><BR/>Without the burden of 6.66 billion people using the planet as a giant feedlot to concern themselves with, they may even succeed in their continuing evolution.<BR/><BR/>Maybe a cigar is just a cigar though, and it's just about psychopaths getting off on exercising power to get more power.</p>
