<dd class='comment-body'>
<p>kikz - Lincoln being the Feds bitch seems a bit strong, or more accurately a bitch of the Money Power.<BR/><BR/>Near the close of the war, in reply to a letter from a friend in Illinois, President Lincoln said:<BR/><BR/>" It has been indeed a trying hour for the republic ; but I see in the near future, a crisis approaching that unnerves me and causes me to tremble for the safety of my country. As a result of the war corporations have been enthroned and an era of corruption in high places will follow, and the money power of the country will endeavor to prolong its reign by working upon the prejudices of the people until all wealth is aggregated in a few hands, and the Republic is destroyed. <BR/><BR/>I feel at this moment more anxiety for the safety of my country than ever before, even in the midst of war. God grant that my suspicions may prove groundless."<BR/><BR/>Doesn't sound too happy with the Money Power, maybe an ungrateful bitch.<BR/><BR/>Besides,  London Money Powers and their agents on Wall Street would not lend Lincoln money at less than 30% interest, so he flipped them the bird and issued greenbacks.  Initially the greenbacks were to be issued without exception under the Legal Tender Act, but USTS Chase and the Senate then was bought off to add an exception for paying tarriffs and interest on public debt, which caused it's devaluation.  They were issued without debt and not through a central bank.<BR/>     <BR/>Lincoln did support a Central Bank, primarily to fund the railroads which was his passion.  But the National Banking Act was the product of a corrupt Congress and the USTS Chase who supported the exception clause making it necessary to borrow from the banks controlled by the Money Powers in London.  It was legalized theft.  Lincoln was likely deceived by USTS Chase or did not fully understand this National Banking Act which allowed the banks to create their own money by buying bonds held on deposit by the UST, which earned them interest, and then getting 90% of the money back to loan out to others, earning more interest.  <BR/><BR/>Chase later went to the Supreme Court and ruled that the Legal Tender Act was unconstitutional. This was the good Act, especially  in it's orginal form in the House.  <BR/><BR/>Lincoln was a Hamiltonian, but some of what he did was a result of the war.  I am hardly a Hamiltonian, but this was a war that needed fighting, and some of the actions may have been warranted given the British and French threat.<BR/><BR/>The Money Powers in London and their agents on Wall Street were upset with Lincolns greenbacks.  He issued 400 million of them saving over 4 billion in interest or lost profits for the Money Powers.<BR/><BR/>They were also upset at his alliance with Russia to prevent the British and French from interfering with Lincolns blockade.  The British had recently been at war with Russia. The cost of the Czars protection was buying Alaska, to pay the debt without knowing about it we bough it.  It was knwn as Sewells Folly, paying good money for a big block of ice with a few polar bears and eskimos on it.<BR/><BR/>The Civil War was a plan by the Money Powers in London to divide the US and have 2 central banks, one in the south and one in the north, and have both sides contantly at war with each other.  They were not happy the North won this war, and credit has to go to Lincoln.   <BR/><BR/>When it became obvious the North would win, and Lincoln would prevent the Money Powers agents on Wall Street from descending on the South, the decision was made to get rid of him.<BR/><BR/>Lincoln and the Czar were both killed, although the Czar was done in for a different reason by Lenins brother, as he was an obstacle to the plans for Communism in Russia.<BR/><BR/>The Knights of the Golden Circle were formed in 1854, although some elements were known under other names since 1833 when attempts were made on Jacksons life for blocking the renewal of the 2nd national bank.  They were also implicated in Lincolns assassination.  <BR/><BR/>But once the plan to divide the US by the Money Powers was approved, which was in 1857,  the Knights of the Golden Circle were used to encourage the Southern States to secede and set up their own banks in each state.  <BR/><BR/>So the Civil War was a great conspiracy, and as you said, led to much of the evil we see today.  The end of slavery was a good thing, but the Money Power through their agent Albert Pike set up the KKK to prevent the blacks from integrating with whites, and these racial tensions that still exist today are likely to be used by the Money Power in the coming years to rock this country again.<BR/><BR/>But lets not blame it all on Lincoln being the Feds bitch.<BR/><BR/>And Rockwell/Ron Paul are controlled dissident agents of the Money Power.  The Gold Standard would destroy this countries ability to rebuild after they destroy our currency and economy.  Thats what the Money Power wants, and thats why Ron Paul got the press and funding he did, limited though it was.  So do not believe everything you read there (there are some nuggets among the disinformation pieces).</p>
